Afterword

If you told me a year ago that I would write a book — especially one this long, and about the universe and philosophy — I would’ve laughed in disbelief.

This is the first book I’ve ever written in my life, and now I know: finishing a book is no small task.

During the writing process, my eye inflammation (iritis) came back. It made writing especially difficult.

And I had zero knowledge of formatting or publishing — from fonts,  to design tone, to layout — I had to learn everything from scratch. I made lots of mistakes, and fixed them as I went.

Honestly, if I had tried to write this book just a few years ago — before AI tools were widely available — I probably wouldn’t have been able to do it.

My writing skills alone wouldn’t have been enough.

I know that philosophy books don’t usually have a big audience.

This might not be a popular book. But that’s okay — I never wrote it for the market.

I wrote it because I wanted to record some of the thoughts and patterns I found while reflecting on life, the universe, and time.

And if reading this book sparked something in you — if you feel curious or want to explore more — I sincerely invite you to visit my website and start a conversation with me.

Maybe we can discover even more possibilities together.

Thank you for reading all the way to the end.

Your support will help this book reach farther and connect with more readers. May this book help you understand the world a bit more — and encourage you to be someone who chooses kindness.

Because in a limited world, choosing kindness is already a way of changing it.
